<Layout::Text text-l text-f>
    <h2>Datetimes</h2>
	<p>SurrealDB has native support for dates and times with nanosecond precision.</p>
</Layout::Text>

<Layout::Gap mini />

<Layout::Text text-l text-f>
	<h3>Dates</h3>
	<p>SurrealDB automatically parses and understands dates which are written as strings in the SurrealQL language. Dates must be formatted in an <Link @link="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601">ISO-8601</Link> format. Datetimes which are specified without the time part, will automatically default to the beginning of the date.</p>
	<Code @name="docs-datamodel-datetimes-date.sql">
		CREATE person SET birthday = "1990-06-22";
	</Code>
</Layout::Text>

